# TypeScript Best Practices

## TypeScript Standards
- Use TypeScript for all files (`.ts`, `.tsx`)
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use strict type checking - NO `any` types
- Implement proper error boundaries with typed error states
- Use generic types for reusable components
- Prefer `const assertions` and `satisfies` operator when appropriate

## Naming Conventions
- Use PascalCase for components and interfaces
- Use camelCase for functions and variables
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Prefix custom hooks with "use"
- Suffix type definitions with "Type" when needed
